1  - Create Folder             =>  mkdir newFolder
2  - Create File               =>  touch newFile
3  - Remove Folder             =>  rmdir oldFolder
4  - Remove Folder have files  =>  rm -R oldFolder
5  - Remove File               =>  rm    oldFile
6  - clear                     =>  clear
7  - ls -l                     =>  show folder contain with details
8  - change password           =>  sudo passwd <username>
9  - show version              =>  php -v or php --version
10 - help                      => <package name> --help  // -h

- for Arch Linux
1 - update package  =>  sudo pacman -Syy

pacman package

1 - install program =>  sudo pacman -S < name of package >
2 - remove program  =>  sudo pacman -R < name of package >

- Another
1 - whoami  =>  pc name
2 - cmatrix =>  form (need install from pacman)
3 - sl      =>  form (need install from pacman)
4 - top     => data about cpu and ram (need install)


*output of ls -l : d rwx r-x --x
    d   = (direction)
    rwx = (Read Write Excute)
    l   = it's link for folder in another place